RCW 79.44.003

"Assessing district" defined.

As used in this chapter "assessing district" means:(1) Incorporated cities and towns;(2) Diking districts;(3) Drainage districts;(4) Port districts;(5) Irrigation districts;(6) Water-sewer districts;(7) Counties;(8) Weed boards and weed districts; and(9) Any municipal corporation or public agency having power to levy local improvement or other assessments, rates, or charges which by statute are expressly made applicable to lands of the state.

As used in this chapter "assessing district" means:

(1) Incorporated cities and towns;

(2) Diking districts;

(3) Drainage districts;

(4) Port districts;

(5) Irrigation districts;

(6) Water-sewer districts;

(7) Counties;

(8) Weed boards and weed districts; and

(9) Any municipal corporation or public agency having power to levy local improvement or other assessments, rates, or charges which by statute are expressly made applicable to lands of the state.

[ 2021 c 217 s 15; 1999 c 153 s 68; 1989 c 243 s 13; 1971 ex.s. c 234 s 14; 1963 c 20 s 1.]

